WEBVTT

00:00:12.583 --> 00:00:17.292
"March 6, 2024"       "Floor 56: Pani"

00:00:26.458 --> 00:00:29.333
We'll lure the Field Boss
into the village.

00:00:30.875 --> 00:00:32.875
W-Wait a second.

00:00:32.875 --> 00:00:34.833
If we do something like
that, the villagers...

00:00:34.833 --> 00:00:36.333
That's the goal.

00:00:36.333 --> 00:00:38.875
While the boss is killing NPCs,

00:00:38.875 --> 00:00:41.208
we're going to attack it,
and then destroy it.

00:00:41.708 --> 00:00:44.958
NPCs aren't just 3-D objects
like trees or rocks.

00:00:45.375 --> 00:00:46.208
They're...

00:00:46.208 --> 00:00:48.167
Alive? Is that it?

00:00:50.042 --> 00:00:51.875
They're only objects.

00:00:52.292 --> 00:00:56.000
Even if they're killed,
they'll just respawn.

00:00:56.625 --> 00:00:59.125
I can't go along with
that kind of plan.

00:01:00.458 --> 00:01:04.083
It's been decided that this
operation will be run by myself,

00:01:04.083 --> 00:01:06.917
Asuna, vice commander of the
Knights of the Blood Oath.

00:01:07.708 --> 00:01:10.000
You will obey my orders.

00:01:19.083 --> 00:01:20.292
Hey.

00:01:20.292 --> 00:01:21.792
You two got into it again, huh?

00:01:21.792 --> 00:01:22.833
Agil?

00:01:22.833 --> 00:01:27.250
You and the second-in-command...
why are you always like that?

00:01:27.250 --> 00:01:29.208
We just don't have
good chemistry.

00:01:30.333 --> 00:01:32.083
You can become powerful.

00:01:32.083 --> 00:01:36.667
So if someone you trust ever
invites you to join a guild,

00:01:36.667 --> 00:01:38.083
don't turn them down.

00:01:38.083 --> 00:01:39.792
That's what I said,

00:01:39.792 --> 00:01:44.042
but who knew that she'd turn into
a floor-clearing demon in the top guild?

00:01:56.417 --> 00:02:00.875
<i>The cowardly past that I'd acknowledged</i>

00:02:01.208 --> 00:02:06.708
<i>Still not understanding why,</i>

00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:17.542
<i>I stand behind myself, scared</i>
<i>Projecting reality onto today</i>

00:02:17.875 --> 00:02:22.875
<i>I've drawn so many skies</i>

00:02:23.208 --> 00:02:27.542
<i>This must be my fleeting heart</i>

00:02:27.875 --> 00:02:30.250
<i>Out of control</i>

00:02:30.583 --> 00:02:35.833
<i>In my dreams, this body soars so high</i>

00:02:36.167 --> 00:02:41.042
<i>And it can brush away any fears that cling to me</i>

00:02:41.458 --> 00:02:47.625
<i>Asleep inside me, these budding</i>
<i>feelings start to expand</i>

00:02:47.958 --> 00:02:51.542
<i>I realize this, weak as I am...</i>
<i>As long as I had you</i>

00:02:51.875 --> 00:02:56.833
<i>I could stay strong in this dark world</i>

00:02:57.167 --> 00:03:02.833
<i>My heart will dream a long dream forever</i>

00:03:03.750 --> 00:03:06.208
<i>I want to always be with you</i>

00:03:06.542 --> 00:03:11.875
<i>I'll give you everything I have...</i>

00:03:14.958 --> 00:03:18.958
"Murder in the Safe Zone"

00:03:23.083 --> 00:03:27.083
"April 11, 2024"       "Floor 59: Danac"

00:03:31.500 --> 00:03:32.833
What are you doing?

00:03:39.000 --> 00:03:41.250
Oh. It's only you.

00:03:41.250 --> 00:03:44.875
Everyone else in the Assault Team is
going all out to clear the dungeon, so...

00:03:44.875 --> 00:03:47.875
What are you doing
taking a nap out here?

00:03:48.417 --> 00:03:50.875
Even solo players need to
take this more seriously--

00:03:50.875 --> 00:03:53.625
Not only is this Aincrad's
nicest season,

00:03:53.625 --> 00:03:55.833
but today's weather is
at its optimum setting.

00:03:57.375 --> 00:04:00.292
Diving into a dungeon on a
day like this is a waste.

00:04:00.292 --> 00:04:02.875
Do you even understand
what's going on?

00:04:02.875 --> 00:04:07.833
Every day we waste here is one
more we've lost in the real world.

00:04:07.833 --> 00:04:12.542
But right now, the place where
we're alive is here in Aincrad.

00:04:16.375 --> 00:04:17.500
See?

00:04:17.500 --> 00:04:20.417
The wind and sunlight feel so good.

00:04:20.917 --> 00:04:22.125
Do they?

00:04:22.458 --> 00:04:24.542
Isn't the weather always the same?

00:04:25.667 --> 00:04:29.292
If you were to lie down
like me, you'd understand.

00:05:10.250 --> 00:05:12.375
Hey, take a look at that.

00:05:12.375 --> 00:05:13.958
Taking a nap at this time of day?

00:05:13.958 --> 00:05:15.708
Some people don't have
a care in the world.

00:05:15.708 --> 00:05:17.958
Who are they? Jeez...

00:05:19.792 --> 00:05:22.000
I didn't think she'd really fall asleep.

00:05:50.958 --> 00:05:53.750
Wh... What...

00:05:53.750 --> 00:05:54.833
Morning.

00:05:54.833 --> 00:05:56.000
Sleep well?

00:06:06.542 --> 00:06:08.167
One meal...

00:06:09.750 --> 00:06:11.125
A meal!

00:06:11.125 --> 00:06:13.333
I'll treat you one time
to anything you want.

00:06:13.333 --> 00:06:15.167
Then we'll be even! Deal?

00:06:17.625 --> 00:06:20.583
"Floor 57: Martin"

00:06:27.292 --> 00:06:29.708
Isn't that Asuna from the
Knights of the Blood Oath?

00:06:30.333 --> 00:06:32.125
She's the Lightning Flash...

00:06:32.125 --> 00:06:34.000
Who's the guy dressed in black?

00:06:35.333 --> 00:06:37.375
Well, anyway...

00:06:38.042 --> 00:06:40.125
Thanks for today.

00:06:41.375 --> 00:06:42.958
For watching over me.

00:06:42.958 --> 00:06:44.417
Ah, no problem...

00:06:44.708 --> 00:06:47.542
The towns are safe areas,

00:06:47.542 --> 00:06:52.000
so no one can attack
or player kill you.

00:06:52.625 --> 00:06:54.792
The only exception is
when you're asleep.

00:06:54.792 --> 00:06:55.833
Yeah.

00:06:55.833 --> 00:06:58.875
Sleep PKs, which abuse
the duel system.

00:06:59.458 --> 00:07:02.958
Normally, duels are held
only as tests of strength.

00:07:03.500 --> 00:07:04.708
But during a duel,

00:07:04.708 --> 00:07:08.625
HP can go down, even in a safe zone,
and you can sustain damage.

00:07:10.125 --> 00:07:12.833
So you can challenge
a sleeping person,

00:07:12.833 --> 00:07:16.667
manipulating that person's finger
to click the OK button.

00:07:17.292 --> 00:07:19.625
Then you just keep
attacking one-sidedly.

00:07:20.042 --> 00:07:22.333
Such incidents have
occurred before.

00:07:23.417 --> 00:07:25.125
So, well...

00:07:25.708 --> 00:07:26.792
Thank you.

00:07:27.208 --> 00:07:29.042
W-Well...

00:07:29.042 --> 00:07:31.417
Y-You're welcome.

00:07:51.625 --> 00:07:52.750
Hurry and pull it out!

00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:02.792
You stay down here
and catch him.

00:08:02.792 --> 00:08:03.792
Got it.

00:08:04.750 --> 00:08:05.750
Hang on!

00:08:08.958 --> 00:08:09.958
Damn it...

00:08:25.167 --> 00:08:26.833
<i>To die inside a safe zone...</i>

00:08:26.833 --> 00:08:28.917
<i>there's no other way except</i>
<i>to be defeated in a duel.</i>

00:08:30.208 --> 00:08:31.208
<i>That means...</i>

00:08:31.458 --> 00:08:32.458
Everyone!

00:08:32.458 --> 00:08:34.708
Look for the "duel winner" icon!

00:08:36.500 --> 00:08:38.542
There's no one inside.

00:08:52.417 --> 00:08:55.250
What's the deal here?

00:08:55.250 --> 00:08:57.250
The obvious conclusion

00:08:57.250 --> 00:09:00.750
is that the challenger impaled
the victim with that spear,

00:09:00.750 --> 00:09:04.083
put a noose around his neck,
and pushed him out this window.

00:09:04.750 --> 00:09:06.083
Wouldn't you agree?

00:09:06.083 --> 00:09:09.083
But there was no sign
of the winner icon.

00:09:09.458 --> 00:09:10.708
That's impossible.

00:09:10.708 --> 00:09:14.667
The only way to inflict damage on
someone in a safe area is via a duel.

00:09:20.417 --> 00:09:23.708
Either way, we can't ignore this.

00:09:24.208 --> 00:09:25.167
Yeah.

00:09:25.167 --> 00:09:29.625
If someone's found a way to
PK within safe areas,

00:09:29.625 --> 00:09:34.167
that would make it dangerous not only
outside towns, but inside as well.

00:09:34.167 --> 00:09:35.458
You're right.

00:09:36.333 --> 00:09:40.083
It'll mean leaving the front lines,
but I guess there's no choice?

00:09:42.750 --> 00:09:46.292
In that case, you're going to cooperate
with me until we've resolved this.

00:09:46.292 --> 00:09:49.208
Just so we're completely clear,
there won't be any time for napping.

00:09:49.667 --> 00:09:51.875
You're the one who was napping.

00:10:05.292 --> 00:10:06.417
Excuse me.

00:10:06.417 --> 00:10:09.125
If any of you saw what just
happened from the start,

00:10:09.125 --> 00:10:11.000
we'd like you to please speak up!

00:10:14.458 --> 00:10:15.958
By the time I got here...

00:10:17.750 --> 00:10:20.875
Sorry, I know you've just had
a frightening experience.

00:10:21.417 --> 00:10:22.917
What's your name?

00:10:23.958 --> 00:10:26.958
Um... my name is Yolko...

00:10:26.958 --> 00:10:30.167
By any chance, were you the one
who let out that first scream?

00:10:30.167 --> 00:10:31.458
Y-Yes.

00:10:31.458 --> 00:10:34.458
I just came here to have dinner

00:10:34.458 --> 00:10:36.750
with the man who was killed.

00:10:37.333 --> 00:10:39.917
His name is Kains.

00:10:40.167 --> 00:10:42.792
We used to be in the same guild.

00:10:43.250 --> 00:10:45.750
But we got separated in the plaza.

00:10:46.125 --> 00:10:47.792
I looked around,

00:10:47.792 --> 00:10:50.833
and I saw him hanging from
the church window...

00:10:53.792 --> 00:10:55.750
Did you see anyone
else at that time?

00:10:57.333 --> 00:10:59.125
It was just for a second,

00:10:59.125 --> 00:11:03.083
but I thought I saw someone
standing behind Kains.

00:11:04.792 --> 00:11:07.250
Did that person look familiar?

00:11:08.875 --> 00:11:10.583
No...

00:11:10.583 --> 00:11:13.458
Um... I hate to ask this...

00:11:13.458 --> 00:11:15.542
But does anything
come to mind?

00:11:15.542 --> 00:11:18.250
The reason why someone
would've wanted to kill Kains?

00:11:31.458 --> 00:11:34.917
Sorry to make you walk
with me all this way.

00:11:34.917 --> 00:11:36.042
Don't worry about it.

00:11:36.042 --> 00:11:39.708
Anyway, we'd like you to talk
to us again tomorrow, okay?

00:11:39.708 --> 00:11:40.708
Okay...

00:11:45.833 --> 00:11:47.667
So, now what?

00:11:48.125 --> 00:11:50.417
Let's review what we
know right now.

00:11:51.417 --> 00:11:53.917
If we learn where that
spear came from,

00:11:53.917 --> 00:11:56.417
it might lead us
to the perpetrator.

00:11:56.417 --> 00:11:59.333
Then we'll need someone
with the appraisal skill.

00:11:59.333 --> 00:12:02.333
You don't... have it, obviously.

00:12:02.333 --> 00:12:03.375
Of course not.

00:12:03.375 --> 00:12:04.875
Nor do you.

00:12:04.875 --> 00:12:08.500
Also... must you address me so curtly?

00:12:08.500 --> 00:12:09.958
U-Um...

00:12:09.958 --> 00:12:11.917
Well, maybe...

00:12:11.917 --> 00:12:13.500
"Miss" then?

00:12:14.208 --> 00:12:15.417
Or "Lady Vice Commander"?

00:12:16.708 --> 00:12:17.708
"Lady Lightning Flash"?

00:12:20.875 --> 00:12:22.958
You can just call me Asuna.

00:12:23.417 --> 00:12:25.083
S-Sure thing.

00:12:25.083 --> 00:12:29.042
Anyway, about that appraisal skill...
do any of your friends have it?

00:12:30.042 --> 00:12:32.750
I do have a friend who's a weapons
merchant with that skill...

00:12:32.750 --> 00:12:34.917
But this is their busiest time,

00:12:34.917 --> 00:12:36.875
so I don't think I
can ask soon...

00:12:37.167 --> 00:12:38.167
I see.

00:12:38.167 --> 00:12:41.458
Then why don't we ask an
item merchant that I know?

00:12:41.708 --> 00:12:44.958
"Floor 50: Algade"

00:12:48.542 --> 00:12:50.958
Thank you! Come again, brother!

00:12:53.208 --> 00:12:56.625
I can see you're running as
ruthless a business as ever.

00:12:57.250 --> 00:12:59.333
Hey, that you, Kirito?

00:12:59.333 --> 00:13:04.083
Buy cheap and sell cheap.
That's my motto.

00:13:04.083 --> 00:13:06.292
I don't know about
that second part.

00:13:06.292 --> 00:13:08.542
Don't go slandering
my good name.

00:13:11.708 --> 00:13:13.292
Wh-What's happened, Kirito?

00:13:13.292 --> 00:13:17.125
You're a solo player, so what're you
doing here with Asuna of all people?

00:13:17.125 --> 00:13:19.792
I thought you two
didn't get along?

00:13:20.292 --> 00:13:21.500
Spill it!

00:13:22.042 --> 00:13:24.500
Someone's HP dropped to
zero within a safe area?

00:13:24.750 --> 00:13:26.292
And it wasn't a duel?

00:13:26.292 --> 00:13:29.000
No one saw a winner icon.

00:13:29.000 --> 00:13:31.958
If he was walking with
Yolko right before,

00:13:31.958 --> 00:13:34.292
then it's not a sleep PK either.

00:13:34.292 --> 00:13:38.000
The method is too complex
for some random duel.

00:13:38.000 --> 00:13:41.792
We can be certain that
it was a premeditated PK.

00:13:41.792 --> 00:13:43.750
Which brings us to this.

00:13:53.167 --> 00:13:54.792
It's a player-made weapon.

00:13:54.792 --> 00:13:55.500
Really?

00:13:55.500 --> 00:13:57.542
Who is it? The one who made it?

00:13:57.542 --> 00:13:59.250
Grimlock.

00:13:59.250 --> 00:14:00.792
Never heard of him...

00:14:01.292 --> 00:14:03.708
Not any top-ranked bladesmith,
I can tell you that.

00:14:03.708 --> 00:14:06.417
And there's nothing particularly
unusual about the weapon.

00:14:06.417 --> 00:14:08.750
But it should still be a clue.

00:14:09.875 --> 00:14:12.167
Tell us its item name, too.

00:14:12.167 --> 00:14:13.292
Let's see...

00:14:13.292 --> 00:14:17.875
Guilty Thorn is its listed name.
In other words, "thorn of sin."

00:14:20.083 --> 00:14:22.333
Thorn of sin...

00:14:32.292 --> 00:14:33.500
Okay...

00:14:36.500 --> 00:14:37.583
Wait!

00:14:40.542 --> 00:14:41.542
Why?

00:14:41.542 --> 00:14:43.042
What do you mean, why?

00:14:43.417 --> 00:14:44.500
Are you stupid?

00:14:44.500 --> 00:14:47.000
That weapon's already
killed someone!

00:14:47.000 --> 00:14:50.667
But we can't be sure
unless we try.

00:14:50.667 --> 00:14:53.083
Stop doing reckless
things like that!

00:14:53.083 --> 00:14:56.583
As for this... Agil, please
hold on to it for us.

00:14:56.583 --> 00:14:57.792
Huh? Sure...

00:15:00.333 --> 00:15:02.833
"The Next Day"

00:15:09.542 --> 00:15:11.458
Tell us, Yolko,

00:15:11.458 --> 00:15:15.125
have you ever heard
the name "Grimlock"?

00:15:17.208 --> 00:15:18.250
Yes.

00:15:18.250 --> 00:15:22.958
He was a member of the guild that
Kains and I once belonged to.

00:15:24.375 --> 00:15:28.167
When we had that black spear
stuck in Kains's chest appraised,

00:15:28.167 --> 00:15:32.083
we found out that it was
made by this Grimlock.

00:15:34.208 --> 00:15:37.000
Can you think of any reason why?

00:15:39.167 --> 00:15:41.167
Yes, I can.

00:15:42.292 --> 00:15:46.167
I'm sorry I wasn't able
to tell you yesterday.

00:15:46.167 --> 00:15:47.625
I wanted to forget...

00:15:47.625 --> 00:15:50.542
It's something I don't really
want to remember.

00:15:51.792 --> 00:15:54.208
But I'm going to tell you.

00:15:55.625 --> 00:15:59.583
That was what destroyed our guild...

00:16:03.458 --> 00:16:06.917
Our guild's name was Golden Apple.

00:16:08.208 --> 00:16:09.250
Six months ago,

00:16:10.000 --> 00:16:12.542
a rare monster that
we happened to defeat

00:16:12.542 --> 00:16:16.042
dropped a powerful ring
that raised agility by 20.

00:16:16.958 --> 00:16:19.333
We were divided on whether
to use it for the guild,

00:16:19.333 --> 00:16:22.417
or sell it and split the earnings.

00:16:23.250 --> 00:16:26.792
But in the end,
we put it to a vote.

00:16:27.542 --> 00:16:30.958
The vote went 5-3
in favor of selling it.

00:16:32.042 --> 00:16:36.167
Our leader, Griselda,
was going to stay overnight

00:16:36.167 --> 00:16:39.917
at a large town on the front lines
to give it to a broker.

00:16:40.875 --> 00:16:44.875
But... she never came back.

00:16:48.208 --> 00:16:53.542
Later, we learned that
Griselda had died.

00:16:54.042 --> 00:16:57.542
To this day, I still don't
know how she died.

00:16:58.250 --> 00:17:02.667
No one would leave a safe zone
with that kind of rare item on them.

00:17:02.667 --> 00:17:05.458
Meaning that it was a sleep PK?

00:17:05.458 --> 00:17:09.167
Six months ago would have been just
before the method really spread.

00:17:09.458 --> 00:17:12.458
But it's hard to think
it's a coincidence.

00:17:12.833 --> 00:17:17.333
Whoever attacked her must have been
a player who knew about the ring.

00:17:17.792 --> 00:17:19.125
In other words...

00:17:19.125 --> 00:17:23.250
One of the other seven
members of Golden Apple...

00:17:24.333 --> 00:17:28.500
The most obvious suspects would be
those who opposed selling it.

00:17:28.875 --> 00:17:31.833
You mean they
attacked Griselda

00:17:31.833 --> 00:17:34.708
to get the ring
before it was sold?

00:17:34.708 --> 00:17:36.167
Probably.

00:17:36.625 --> 00:17:38.542
Who's Grimlock?

00:17:38.542 --> 00:17:41.875
He was Griselda's husband.

00:17:41.875 --> 00:17:45.083
Just within the game of course.

00:17:45.833 --> 00:17:48.833
Griselda was a powerful
swordswoman.

00:17:48.833 --> 00:17:51.333
Beautiful... And smart....

00:17:52.208 --> 00:17:56.292
Grimlock was a kind man
who was always smiling.

00:17:56.875 --> 00:18:00.625
They made a great couple,
and they got along well.

00:18:01.458 --> 00:18:05.708
If Grimlock was the one responsible
for yesterday's murder,

00:18:05.708 --> 00:18:10.667
he must be after the three who
voted against selling the ring.

00:18:12.000 --> 00:18:17.083
Two of the three who were opposed to
selling the ring were myself and Kains.

00:18:18.000 --> 00:18:19.333
Then who's the other?

00:18:19.750 --> 00:18:21.875
A tank named Schmitt.

00:18:21.875 --> 00:18:26.708
I've heard he's on the front lines now
with the Holy Dragon Alliance.

00:18:26.708 --> 00:18:27.958
Schmitt?

00:18:28.250 --> 00:18:29.667
I've heard that name...

00:18:29.958 --> 00:18:32.750
He leads the Holy Dragon
Alliance's defense forces.

00:18:33.125 --> 00:18:34.667
He's a large-lance user.

00:18:36.083 --> 00:18:37.875
Oh, him.

00:18:37.875 --> 00:18:40.000
You know Schmitt?

00:18:40.000 --> 00:18:43.375
Well, I've only run into him
a few times while clearing bosses.

00:18:43.375 --> 00:18:46.542
Could you possibly
let me see Schmitt?

00:18:46.542 --> 00:18:49.875
He probably hasn't heard
about what occurred.

00:18:50.292 --> 00:18:54.125
And if that's the case, what happened
to Kains could happen to him too...

00:18:56.625 --> 00:18:58.833
Let's summon Schmitt.

00:18:58.833 --> 00:19:01.208
I know someone at the
Holy Dragon Alliance.

00:19:01.208 --> 00:19:03.917
If we go to their HQ,
I think we'll find a way.

00:19:03.917 --> 00:19:07.167
First, we should walk
Yolko back to her inn.

00:19:07.583 --> 00:19:12.542
Yolko, don't leave
the inn until we return.

00:19:13.083 --> 00:19:14.083
All right.

00:19:20.125 --> 00:19:24.375
How do you think this safe-zone
murder was carried out?

00:19:24.375 --> 00:19:26.583
I see three possibilities...

00:19:26.583 --> 00:19:29.667
The first is a fair duel.

00:19:30.000 --> 00:19:35.042
The second is through a system exploit
that combines known methods.

00:19:35.042 --> 00:19:37.042
Yes, something like that.

00:19:37.042 --> 00:19:38.250
And the third?

00:19:38.917 --> 00:19:42.250
Some unknown skill, which bypasses
the protection of the safe areas.

00:19:42.250 --> 00:19:44.375
Or possibly an item.

00:19:44.750 --> 00:19:48.333
No, the third is impossible.

00:19:48.333 --> 00:19:49.250
Why?

00:19:49.250 --> 00:19:50.542
Because it's unfair.

00:19:51.083 --> 00:19:53.500
I kind of hate to admit it,

00:19:53.500 --> 00:19:57.417
but SAO's rules are essentially fair.

00:19:57.417 --> 00:20:01.875
There's no way that this game
would allow murders in safe areas.

00:20:11.750 --> 00:20:16.292
Is it true that Kains was killed
with Grimlock's weapon?

00:20:18.042 --> 00:20:19.208
It is.

00:20:20.333 --> 00:20:23.000
Why would Kains be killed
after all this time?

00:20:23.000 --> 00:20:24.000
He...

00:20:24.000 --> 00:20:25.792
Did he steal the ring?

00:20:26.208 --> 00:20:28.792
Was he the one
who killed Griselda?

00:20:29.792 --> 00:20:32.542
Does Grimlock plan
to kill the three of us

00:20:32.542 --> 00:20:34.375
who opposed selling the ring?

00:20:34.375 --> 00:20:36.500
Is he after you and me too?

00:20:36.500 --> 00:20:42.250
It could be another member, for
whom Grimlock made the spear.

00:20:42.250 --> 00:20:46.792
Or perhaps it may be
Griselda's revenge...

00:20:47.708 --> 00:20:50.875
Because no one could kill
someone inside a safe zone

00:20:50.875 --> 00:20:53.250
unless they were a ghost.

00:20:56.125 --> 00:21:00.417
I stayed awake all
last night thinking...

00:21:01.375 --> 00:21:06.833
In the end, you could say it was all of us
guild members who killed Griselda!

00:21:06.833 --> 00:21:10.750
When that ring dropped,
we shouldn't have ever voted...

00:21:10.750 --> 00:21:14.292
We should've just done what
Griselda told us to do!

00:21:17.375 --> 00:21:24.208
Grimlock was the only one who said
we should just leave it to Griselda.

00:21:24.792 --> 00:21:29.208
So he has the right
to take revenge

00:21:29.208 --> 00:21:32.500
for Griselda on the rest of us.

00:21:33.667 --> 00:21:35.250
You're kidding me.

00:21:35.250 --> 00:21:36.542
You're kidding me...

00:21:36.958 --> 00:21:40.000
After all this time,
six whole months...

00:21:40.000 --> 00:21:41.708
Why now?

00:21:41.708 --> 00:21:44.083
You're okay with this, Yolko?

00:21:44.083 --> 00:21:47.292
You're okay with being killed
in such an insane way?

00:22:08.333 --> 00:22:09.333
Yolko!

00:22:30.042 --> 00:22:41.500
The tolling of the faraway bells
sounded a little lonely to me

00:22:41.833 --> 00:22:53.375
So I tried harder, one more time,
this time soaring higher, all the way up

00:22:53.792 --> 00:22:59.333
<i>Neither this reality that just keeps repeating itself</i>

00:22:59.667 --> 00:23:05.125
<i>Nor all my wishes, as numerous as the stars</i>

00:23:05.542 --> 00:23:10.542
<i>Now that I've found the tomorrow</i>
<i>I should strive for</i>

00:23:10.875 --> 00:23:15.833
<i>None of them can overcome these feelings of mine</i>

00:23:16.167 --> 00:23:22.625
<i>A world without end, opening up before my eyes</i>

00:23:22.958 --> 00:23:26.583
<i>Even if it's no more than a dream</i>

00:23:27.167 --> 00:23:33.917
<i>Even if I'm still lost, deep in my heart, it is strong</i>

00:23:34.250 --> 00:23:39.708
<i>Echoing forever and ever</i>

00:23:40.042 --> 00:23:46.208
<i>Shining softly, ever so softly</i>

00:23:47.000 --> 00:23:53.067
Next Time: "Illusionary Avenger."
